<dl id="n12203g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12203g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12203g"> 203(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> il dit ensuite</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[&lsquo;<i>Un p&egrave;re a toujours raison</i>&rsquo;]</font> Il <font color="green">[re]</font>vint <font color="green">[chez lui]</font> en disant: &ldquo;Papa!&rdquo; <mark>Il dit <font color="green">[ensuite]</font></mark>: &ldquo;Un enfant assure son bonheur en &eacute;coutant la parole de son p&egrave;re.&rdquo; <br><font color="green">[He returned home saying &ldquo;Papa!&rdquo; Then he said, &ldquo;A child brings happiness on himself when it listens to his father.&rdquo;]</font> <small> Maurice Delafosse, <a name="LNEG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LNEG"><cite title="source">L'&acirc;me n&egrave;gre</cite></a> (1922) 27</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
